Rip notes: nothing was ripped

Get behind the wheel of one of the most worlds most prestigious cars, the F355 Ferrari, in this conversion of Sega's arcade game. F355 features a number of game modes namely, the Arcade mode which is the same as the checkpoint arcade version; Championship mode where you race 6 races for the combined highest score; Single play which is the same as Arcade mode but with no time limit; Versus play with a two player split screen. The game features 3 levels of difficulty. There are also four Assist functions. Stability Control for cornering, Traction Control from the engine to the tires, Anti Lock Brake System to keep the tires from locking during braking and Intelligent Brake System.



Get set to take to the track in the realistic, aggressive racing of F355 Challenge. In case you didn’t know, F355 stands for Ferrari F355 F1 and seasoned driving fans will find much to enjoy in this Dreamcast tribute to the Italian prancing pony. Blaze across lovingly reproduced professional racecourses (some hidden and unlockable) like Long Beach, Sugo, and Monza, as you compete against up to seven computer-controlled opponents. You can also use your four assist systems (like automatic braking) as you race online against worldwide rivals and post your best times.
